# Vendor listing data (carry_class_vendor_data)

Production reads vendors via `DATABASE_URL` when REST and Postgres project refs differ (`shouldFetchVendorsViaDatabase()` in `src/lib/vendors-db.ts`). **Writes must follow the same rule.**

## Tables in scope

`carry_class_vendor_data`, `enriched_vendor_county_listings`, and SQL in `migrations/` that touches vendor listings.

## Before any vendor DB write

1. Run `npm run check:vendor-db-env` and follow its recommendation.
2. On ref mismatch, **only** use `DATABASE_URL` — not Supabase REST, Dashboard on the REST project, or `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL` clients.
3. Set `VENDORS_FETCH_VIA_DATABASE=1` in `.env.local` for local reads (do not commit).

## How to write

```bash
npm run check:vendor-db-env
npx prisma db execute --file migrations/your-file.sql --schema prisma/schema.prisma
```

Also OK: Prisma scripts, `psql "$DATABASE_URL"`, or `pg`.

## Do NOT use for writes (when refs differ)

Supabase JS `.insert/update/upsert`, Dashboard Table Editor on the REST project, or scripts using only `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL`. When refs match, either path works; still prefer `DATABASE_URL` + migrations.

## After production changes

```bash
curl -X POST "$NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL/api/revalidate-vendors" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $CRON_SECRET"
```

See `src/lib/vendors-db.ts`, `migrations/alameda-approved-instructors.sql`, `src/app/api/revalidate-vendors/route.ts`.
